place.name: TOTTINGTON
place.gazetteerText: TOTTINGTON, a parish, with a village, in Wayland district, Norfolk; on the Thetford and Watton railway, 3¾ miles SSW of Watton. It has a post-office under Thetford. Acres, 3,213. Real property, £2,359. Pop., 308. Houses, 61. The property belongs to Lord Walsingham. The living is a vicarage in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £89. Patrons, the Trustees of Chigwell Free Schools. The church is old. There is a national school. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
